<item>
            <title>[LU-14969] Fall back to buffered I/O for unaligned direct I/O</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14969</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SPECStorage test assumes we can do direct i/o at a 512 byte alignment boundary.&#160; This is not the case in Lustre, since we have to be page aligned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easy solution is to do what GPFS and several other file systems do:&lt;br/&gt;
Fall back to buffered I/O in this case.&#160; This is supported behavior in the kernel since at least 2.6.32.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
